description: The Seoul National Science Museum provides visitors with the opportunity to learn about science with easy-to-understand scientific principles. The Science Museum is divided into three major exhibition halls, namely the main exhibition hall centered on life sciences, the industrial technology hall and special exhibition halls focusing on industrial technology. The main pavilion is designed to explain the principles, rules and applications of science to visitors concisely and thoroughly. During the production process, various new events are held in the special exhibition hall.

address: Yeouido Hangang Park 330 Yeouidong-ro, Yeongdeungpo District, Seoul
description: This fall, Yeouido Hangang Park will be painted with gorgeous colors with gorgeous fireworks, colorful lights and lasers. The Seoul City announced that it will hold the "2024 Seoul Light Hangang Light Island Festival" in the Yeouido Hangang Park area from October 4 (Friday) to 13 (Sunday).Last year, the "Light Island Festival" debuted in the Seorae Island area of ​​Banpo Hangang Park. This year, it is planned to be connected with the Seoul World Fireworks Festival (October 5, 2024) held in Yeouido Hangang Park, presenting a new light art that combines lasers and media art.
The back garden of Gyeongdeok Palace is located in Gyeongdeok Palace, South Korea. It is the back garden of ancient Korean queens. It started construction in 1405.
